@node HISTORY "What has been changed and added.."
@prev BUGS
@next TODO
@{fg highlight}DeliList Version History@{fg text}
------------------------

V1.0 - 14/9/94 (@{b}RELEASED:@{ub} 06/03/95)

 - A program to scan directories and sub-directories of mods.
 - Will compile the names to a file readable by ÛDeliTracker2
 - The switch APPEND allows additional mods to be added to a list.

V1.0a - 13/3/95 (@{b}RELEASED:@{ub} 14/3/95)

 - Just a quick bug fix.
 - Fixed bug with incorrect scanning of directories which have spaces in them.
 - Made the program clean up some of it's temporary files in ram.
   (Both Spotted by: Monier Gael)

@endnode

@node TODO "What next then?"
@next GREETS
@prev HISTORY

     I actually havent got any ideas concerning future development for
DeliList  as it does what I want.  Therefore, I could do with @{"feedback" link CONTACT}
from users who want to see extra functionality in the program.

@{b}HOWEVER:@{ub}

     I  have  an  idea  for  an integrated AREXX program that will add
DeliTracker  control  options to Directory Opus.  At the moment, I use
the included AREXX scripts that come with DeliTracker and link each to
a  DOpus button.  I want to combine all of these and add other options
including  playlist  display  and individual module selection from the
DOpus  directory  windows.  We'll have to see how my ideas develop for
this.   If any of you have any ideas concering this idea, feel free to
mail them to @{"me" link CONTACT}.

@endnode

